    "body": "## Purpose\n\nFixes #34845. \n\nWhen chunked prefill is enabled with speculative decoding (MTP) on Qwen3-Next, the GDN attention backend crashes with:\n\n```\nAssertionError: num_decodes: 1, num_spec_decodes: 2\n```\n\n**Root cause**: The GDN attention backend asserts that `num_decodes` and `num_spec_decodes` are mutually exclusive. With chunked prefill + speculative decoding, a batch can violate this: a request's last prefill chunk may have `query_len=1` with no spec tokens (they were correctly discarded in the previous step's `update_draft_token_ids()` because `is_prefill_chunk` was `True`), which gets misclassified as a regular decode while other requests are spec-decodes. The crash happens during this last prefill chunk step itself, not the subsequent decode step (which would have draft tokens available from `post_step()`).\n\n**Fix**: When both `num_decodes > 0` and `num_spec_decodes > 0`, reclassify the non-spec decodes as prefills.\n\n## Test Plan\n\nAdded `tests/v1/attention/test_gdn_metadata_builder.py` — parametrized unit tests for `GDNAttentionMetadataBuilder.build()` classification logic:\n\n- **mixed_decode_and_spec_decode**: The original #34845 crash scenario\n- **pure_spec_decode**: All spec decodes, no reclassification needed\n- **pure_regular_decode**: No spec config, standard decode path\n- **spec_decode_with_real_prefill**: Multi-token prefill + spec decode\n- **prefill_decode_and_spec_decode**: All three types in one batch\n- **multiple_decodes_reclassified**: Multiple non-spec decodes all reclassified\n- **zero_length_padding_with_spec**: Padded sequences excluded from counts\n- **has_initial_state_after_reclassification**: Prefill kernel metadata set correctly\n\n## Test Result\n\nNew added test cases pass",
